Warped Jellies are stronger variants of jellies that require level 52 Slayer to kill. They are found exclusively within the Catacombs of Kourend, both southern and eastern. Warped Jellies will count towards a Jelly Slayer task.

Jellies attack with magical melee, so armour with high magic defence is recommended, such as Karil's armour or black dragonhide. Like their lower levelled counterparts, using Protect from Melee will prevent all damage from them. Warped Jellies in the eastern chamber can be safespotted using the water in the south-east corner of the chamber. They can either be attacked across the body of water, or around the two corners.

On a slayer task the best way to do it is to use AOE attacks like Chinchompas and/or ice barrage.
